@startuml
' M3 barycenter cluster reorder demo. Three top-level packages
' (PkgA / PkgB / PkgC) feed three matching packages (SinkX / SinkY
' / SinkZ) — note the deliberately reversed mapping: A → Z, B → Y,
' C → X.
'
' Pre-barycenter (declaration order):
'   row 0: [PkgA, PkgB, PkgC]
'   row 1: [SinkX, SinkY, SinkZ]
'   edges A→Z, B→Y, C→X all cross each other  → 3 crossings.
'
' With M3 barycenter reorder, row 0 gets re-sorted to match the
' row-1 layout — clusters whose successors land further to the
' right (A → Z is rightmost) drift right; clusters whose successors
' land left (C → X is leftmost) drift left. Result: row 0 becomes
' [PkgC, PkgB, PkgA] and every arrow runs straight down with zero
' crossings.

package "PkgA" {
  class A1
}
package "PkgB" {
  class B1
}
package "PkgC" {
  class C1
}

package "SinkX" {
  class X1
}
package "SinkY" {
  class Y1
}
package "SinkZ" {
  class Z1
}

A1 --> Z1
B1 --> Y1
C1 --> X1
@enduml
